description:
God has promised an abundance of latter rain power to assist His people in finishing the work. But why hasn’t it come? God’s people have been waiting for the outpouring of the latter rain since Pentecost. As a church we have been praying for this latter rain outpouring. The question is, however, do we meet the conditions required for such an outpouring? Dive into this typological application of the parallels between Elijah’s experience on Carmel and the cleansing of the church with the conditions that must be met in our day.
